---
import Image from 'project:components/image/image'
import './product-banner.css'
---

<section
	class="p-product-banner"
	id="product-banner"
	aria-label="product banner"
>
	<div class="x-card">
		<h3 class="x-card_heading">Astro for PowerPoint</h3>
		<div class="x-card_content">
			<p>
				You asked, we listened. Now you can design Astro-compliant mock-ups and
				lo-fi wireframes in secured environments by using our brand new, ASTRO
				UXDS PowerPoint Toolkit!
			</p>
			<p>
				Built from the ground up, in collaboration with designers from all over
				the DoD space, the ASTRO UXDS PowerPoint Toolkit includes all of Astroâ€™s
				components, now optimized for use in Microsoft PowerPoint.
			</p>
		</div>
	</div>
	<div class="x-card">
		<div class="x-card_heading">
			<h3>New for 2025</h3>
		</div>
		<div class="x-card_content">
			<Image
				{...{
					url: '/images/astro.svg#content',
					width: 160,
					height: 68,
				}}
				aria-hidden="true"
			/>
			<div class="x-card_sub-title">
				<Image
					{...{
						url: '/images/astro-sub-title.svg#content',
						width: 188,
						height: 18,
					}}
					aria-hidden="true"
				/>
				<Image
					{...{
						url: '/images/astro-sub-title-ppt-toolkit.svg#content',
						width: 90,
						height: 18,
					}}
					aria-hidden="true"
				/>
			</div>

			<a href="/platforms/astro-toolkit-ppt/">
				<button type="button">Learn More</button>
			</a>
		</div>
	</div>
	<div class="x-card">
		<div class="x-card_content">
			<img src="/images/astro-toolkit-ppt-screen-2.png" alt="ppt-screen" />
		</div>
	</div>
</section>